main event: An unidentified object was tracked on ground radar and visually observed from North Bend, Oregon.
interesting points: The object was initially sighted at 54,000 ft altitude before descending to 50,000 ft.,The object appeared to orbit during its flight,It was tracked for a total of two hours before fading from view.,Radar operators at Roselle, Washington also reported seeing a bright light that matched the object's altitude.,The conclusions suggested it could be a balloon, aircraft, astronomical object, or remain insufficient for evaluation.
